WEBVTT

00:05.266 --> 00:08.095
What will you call that blue?
Cerulean?

00:08.269 --> 00:11.054
- I guess.
- No, no, azure.

00:11.228 --> 00:12.316
Yeah, sure.

00:15.667 --> 00:16.886
I don't want to
be one of those people

00:17.060 --> 00:20.759
who go around telling other
people to smile and cheer up.

00:20.933 --> 00:22.935
But I should smile
and cheer up.

00:23.110 --> 00:26.417
Yeah, well, maybe. Yes.
For the guests.

00:26.591 --> 00:28.724
I know.
It's just...

00:28.898 --> 00:31.422
I really miss Gina.

00:31.596 --> 00:34.382
Hmm, well,

00:34.556 --> 00:36.645
that's another shade of blue.

00:36.819 --> 00:38.168
Yeah.

00:39.996 --> 00:41.737
Come over tonight.

00:41.911 --> 00:43.739
We'll have a breakup
movie marathon.

00:46.220 --> 00:48.613
It's okay.
I'm just not really feeling it.

00:48.787 --> 00:50.398
Okay.

00:50.572 --> 00:52.400
I'll even do a face mask.

00:54.184 --> 00:56.360
No, it's really... It's okay.

00:56.534 --> 00:59.798
Besides, I don't want to
bring down this whole giddy

00:59.972 --> 01:02.845
and in love but finally
not afraid to show it vibe.

01:03.019 --> 01:05.413
- I'm not giddy, thank you.
- Uh-huh.

01:05.587 --> 01:08.459
- Let's go.
- Morning, Elena.

01:08.633 --> 01:09.721
Javier.

01:09.895 --> 01:11.462
- Uh-huh, not giddy.
- No.

01:11.636 --> 01:13.595
Yes, made it to paradise.

01:13.769 --> 01:14.944
Which way to
the infinity pool?

01:15.118 --> 01:17.164
Eh, first the bar,
then the infinity pool.

01:17.338 --> 01:19.383
- Ah.
- Meet Mateo, Shawn, and Eli.

01:19.557 --> 01:21.951
Hello, gentlemen.
I'm Elena Roarke, your host.

01:22.125 --> 01:23.953
This is my associate, Ruby.
- Hi.

01:24.127 --> 01:26.086
And I see that
your bachelor party weekend

01:26.260 --> 01:28.653
has already started.

01:28.827 --> 01:30.046
Oh, yeah.

01:30.220 --> 01:32.048
So which one of you
is getting married?

01:32.222 --> 01:34.268
Oh, that'd be me.
At least that's the plan.

01:34.442 --> 01:36.748
These drunk guys are
my best man and groomsman.

01:38.446 --> 01:39.447
Well, we are delighted
to meet you all.

01:39.621 --> 01:42.363
Ash will get you settled,
and then we'll talk.

01:42.537 --> 01:44.060
Welcome to Fantasy Island.
- Thank you.

01:44.234 --> 01:45.366
Right this way.

01:49.152 --> 01:52.112
So what's the plan for the big
bachelor party blowout?

01:52.286 --> 01:54.897
Casino night
or beer pong Olympics?

01:55.071 --> 01:57.160
Well, they each
get their own fantasy.

01:57.334 --> 01:59.293
Isn't that enough?

02:00.511 --> 02:02.905
Um, we're supposed
to have another guest.

02:03.079 --> 02:04.298
Where's Ms. Reyes?

02:06.778 --> 02:07.562
both: Hmm.

02:12.088 --> 02:13.089
Ms. Reyes?

02:15.657 --> 02:16.962
Hello.

02:17.137 --> 02:19.095
I'm Elena Roarke.
I'm your host.

02:21.402 --> 02:22.968
Are the bros gone?

02:23.143 --> 02:26.407
Mm, well,
welcome to Fantasy Island.

02:40.725 --> 02:43.075
Helene Reyes,
this is my associate Ruby.

02:43.250 --> 02:45.469
- Hi.
- Hey.

02:46.514 --> 02:48.342
Only child of a single mom.

02:48.516 --> 02:50.605
Carrying my own bag since
I was five.

02:50.779 --> 02:52.868
By all means.

02:53.042 --> 02:55.262
So I thought this place
was supposed to be special.

02:55.436 --> 02:56.959
What's up with the dude squad?

02:57.133 --> 02:59.657
Wonderful to meet you too.

02:59.831 --> 03:02.921
I promise you,
the dudes are here for a reason

03:03.095 --> 03:04.749
just like everyone else
who comes to Fantasy Island.

03:04.923 --> 03:06.882
Now, we're gonna go to
my office so we can talk about

03:07.056 --> 03:08.971
why you're here.

03:09.145 --> 03:10.538
After you, please.

03:13.497 --> 03:17.327
Uh... please meet me
in my office in an hour.

03:17.501 --> 03:18.850
We need to
go over the schedule.

03:19.024 --> 03:20.200
Of course.
See you then.

03:23.028 --> 03:26.684
Now, I know you don't
need to go over the schedule.

03:28.425 --> 03:30.993
I was conceived
in the middle of a hurricane.

03:31.167 --> 03:32.429
Hurricane Helene.

03:32.603 --> 03:35.432
Wow, well, that's one way
to weather a storm.

03:35.606 --> 03:36.868
It was in the jungle
in Belize.

03:37.042 --> 03:39.044
My mom thought
she was gonna die that night.

03:39.219 --> 03:41.133
Instead, here I am.

03:41.308 --> 03:42.874
At least that's the story.

03:43.048 --> 03:46.748
- You were meant to be.
- I guess.

03:46.922 --> 03:48.793
You know, it's always
just been the two of us.

03:48.967 --> 03:50.360
Sometimes my friends
would think

03:50.534 --> 03:52.493
that it was sad, but it wasn't.

03:52.667 --> 03:54.582
Well, a family
can look like anything.

03:54.756 --> 03:56.584
It's love that matters.

03:56.758 --> 03:58.542
We would have
pancakes for dinner

03:58.716 --> 04:00.631
and go camping for Christmas.

04:00.805 --> 04:02.198
And then when I was sick,

04:02.372 --> 04:04.461
she would make this big nest
in the middle of her bed

04:04.635 --> 04:05.984
and rub my back
until I fell asleep.

04:06.158 --> 04:07.812
It was pretty perfect.

04:07.986 --> 04:09.858
She sounds wonderful.

04:10.032 --> 04:11.294
She was.

04:12.904 --> 04:15.951
She, uh, she died a year ago.
- Oh.

04:16.125 --> 04:17.909
I am so sorry for your loss.

04:21.086 --> 04:23.045
I've been sleeping with this
under my pillow.

04:25.439 --> 04:28.529
Which I know is stupid,
but whatever.

04:28.703 --> 04:31.793
I don't think
that's stupid at all.

04:31.967 --> 04:34.274
So Helene,
what can the Island do for you?

04:37.189 --> 04:40.410
My fantasy is to find him.

04:40.584 --> 04:44.458
- Your father?
- My biological father.

04:44.632 --> 04:47.722
You know, with my mom gone,
I just feel kind of untethered.

04:47.896 --> 04:50.115
I want to be
connected to something

04:50.290 --> 04:52.596
and, like, what if
I need a kidney?

04:52.770 --> 04:54.555
What do you know about him?

04:54.729 --> 04:56.513
Just that my mom
called him Sunshine,

04:56.687 --> 04:58.602
'cause he was a ray of light
in the hurricane,

04:58.776 --> 05:01.170
and he called her Blue
'cause of her eyes.

05:01.344 --> 05:03.564
But they only spent
that one night together.

05:03.738 --> 05:05.870
Romantic.

05:06.044 --> 05:10.092
Also, apparently he has
a really great smile.

05:10.266 --> 05:12.703
My mom said
I got mine from him.

05:12.877 --> 05:14.923
Well, let's hope the Island
gives you a reason to use it.

05:15.097 --> 05:17.360
- Mm-hmm.
- Come with me.

05:22.496 --> 05:24.280
So what happens now?

05:24.454 --> 05:26.021
What do I do?
- Choose a path.

05:26.195 --> 05:27.283
That's it?

05:27.457 --> 05:28.980
Every fantasy's different, Helene.

05:29.154 --> 05:31.766
Sometimes I have a map
or itinerary.

05:31.940 --> 05:36.640
In your case,
just do what feels right.

05:36.814 --> 05:40.514
Is it possible...
no, I mean there's no way.

05:40.688 --> 05:43.343
My bio dad's not one
of the guys from the plane.

05:43.517 --> 05:45.388
Is he?
- I don't know.

05:45.562 --> 05:46.911
But it is meaningful

05:47.085 --> 05:49.044
that you're all here together,
for what it's worth.

06:01.535 --> 06:02.666
<i>Oh, I know.</i>

06:02.840 --> 06:04.407
<i>What about some yoga
to perk you up?</i>

06:04.581 --> 06:07.584
I'm not really feeling
all bendy, so...

06:07.758 --> 06:10.631
Okay, origami lesson.
Bike ride.

06:11.936 --> 06:13.068
You know what?

06:13.242 --> 06:15.679
I'll plan
Mateo's bachelor party.

06:15.853 --> 06:17.159
That seems like
the opposite of what's gonna

06:17.333 --> 06:19.248
make you feel better
after a breakup.

06:19.422 --> 06:21.946
Well, maybe basking
in somebody's joy

06:22.120 --> 06:24.209
will be good for me.

06:24.384 --> 06:26.777
Okay, but no strippers.

06:26.951 --> 06:28.649
So how does this work?

06:28.823 --> 06:30.738
Do we just, like, blurt out
our fantasies or...

06:30.912 --> 06:32.522
Well, assuming
you're all okay

06:32.696 --> 06:35.133
with your friends hearing
your heart's desires.

06:35.307 --> 06:37.005
Oh, unlike most guys,
we tell each other everything.

06:37.179 --> 06:39.616
Great.
Let's start with you, Shawn.

06:39.790 --> 06:41.183
What can the Island do for you?

06:41.357 --> 06:44.404
- I'm a scaredy-cat.
- Oh, me too.

06:44.578 --> 06:47.058
Also, I'm queer.

06:47.232 --> 06:48.756
Oh, me too!

06:48.930 --> 06:50.801
Hey.

06:50.975 --> 06:54.239
Yeah, coming out in college
was a whole deal,

06:54.414 --> 06:56.764
but luckily these guys
supported me.

06:56.938 --> 06:58.722
- We're not complete jerks.
- Mm.

06:58.896 --> 07:03.248
It felt so good.
Just completely empowering.

07:03.423 --> 07:06.513
But it's like I used up
all my cards in that one act,

07:06.687 --> 07:10.255
and everything else
just still terrifies me.

07:10.430 --> 07:12.954
He has four smoke alarms
in a one-bedroom apartment.

07:13.128 --> 07:16.871
My fantasy is
to be free of fear.

07:17.045 --> 07:19.613
All fear?
I'm not sure that's wise.

07:19.787 --> 07:21.223
Just for a couple days.

07:21.397 --> 07:23.530
I just want to see what it's
like to do whatever I want

07:23.704 --> 07:26.271
without being gripped
by utter terror.

07:26.446 --> 07:28.186
What is it
that you want to do?

07:28.360 --> 07:31.015
Scuba dive, eat weird stuff,

07:31.189 --> 07:34.410
get a tattoo, touch a spider,
just everything.

07:34.584 --> 07:36.412
Okay, well, we can manage
that and maybe a little more.

07:36.586 --> 07:38.370
Mm.

07:38.545 --> 07:41.069
Eli, what about you?

07:41.243 --> 07:43.680
My fantasy
is to be a chick magnet.

07:43.854 --> 07:45.943
Oh.

07:46.117 --> 07:48.729
- You think I'm an ass?
- We don't judge.

07:48.903 --> 07:51.340
I've always been
romantically challenged.

07:51.514 --> 07:53.298
The third wheel,
the funny friend,

07:53.473 --> 07:55.344
the shoulder girls cry on
when they get dumped.

07:55.518 --> 07:57.868
It gets old.
- It's not like you're an ogre.

07:58.042 --> 07:59.653
Yeah and your last
girlfriend was gorgeous

07:59.827 --> 08:01.263
and crazy about you.
- Evelyn.

08:01.437 --> 08:03.483
He unceremoniously dumped her
on Valentine's Day.

08:03.657 --> 08:05.920
She wasn't the one.

08:06.094 --> 08:08.792
Okay, the point is
I've always had to work

08:08.966 --> 08:10.838
for whatever
female attention I get.

08:11.012 --> 08:13.057
For once, I'd like the women
to come to me.

08:13.231 --> 08:14.711
I understand.

08:14.885 --> 08:16.887
I'm sorry, but come on.

08:17.061 --> 08:19.324
I doubt that.

08:19.499 --> 08:20.978
What about
our groom's fantasy?

08:21.152 --> 08:23.067
Tell me.

08:23.241 --> 08:26.636
Have you ever met someone
and just clicked instantly?

08:26.810 --> 08:28.943
Aw, like you
and your fiancée.

08:29.117 --> 08:30.553
He's not talking
about Sophie.

08:30.727 --> 08:33.338
Although I do love Sophie
more than words can say.

08:33.513 --> 08:35.079
I mean, she's the woman
of my dreams.

08:35.253 --> 08:38.300
Uh, except for
the other woman of his dreams.

08:38.474 --> 08:42.826
Years ago, I spent one night
with a woman I met traveling.

08:43.000 --> 08:45.394
We were together
for less than 24 hours,

08:45.568 --> 08:47.135
but I haven't been able
to stop thinking about her.

08:47.309 --> 08:49.790
And I've always wondered...
- What if?

08:49.964 --> 08:53.750
My fantasy is to see her
one last time.

08:53.924 --> 08:58.102
Eli, there is a beautiful
young woman in a yellow bikini,

08:58.276 --> 09:00.844
and she is desperately trying
to get your attention.

09:05.196 --> 09:06.850
It appears I have
somewhere else to be.

09:09.766 --> 09:11.638
If you'll excuse me.
- Okay.

09:11.812 --> 09:13.553
Oh, my...

09:13.727 --> 09:17.252
Mateo, you and I,
we are headed this way.

09:17.426 --> 09:21.343
And I know
a great tattoo place.

09:21.517 --> 09:23.475
Oh, look at that.
No fear.

09:23.650 --> 09:25.434
- Ah!
- Let's go.

09:25.608 --> 09:28.089
Oh, and the bigger the better.
- Okay.

09:33.224 --> 09:35.400
As soon as you step
through that door,

09:35.575 --> 09:36.793
your fantasy will begin.

09:39.361 --> 09:40.928
She's on the other side?

09:42.364 --> 09:43.931
Maybe this is a bad idea.

09:44.105 --> 09:45.802
Only you know
the answer to that.

09:49.676 --> 09:50.590
Whenever you're ready.

10:40.596 --> 10:42.032
Hola.

10:42.206 --> 10:45.340
- Huh, an American.
- Guilty.

10:45.514 --> 10:46.515
Mom?

10:52.260 --> 10:53.914
You know, when you said
go over the schedule,

10:54.088 --> 10:55.176
I didn't picture this.

10:55.350 --> 10:57.657
And to be clear,

10:57.831 --> 10:59.571
I also didn't picture
going over the schedule.

10:59.746 --> 11:02.705
Patience, Javi.

11:07.405 --> 11:09.930
What is this place?

11:10.104 --> 11:12.236
A little secret of mine. Vamos.

11:15.936 --> 11:19.330
Welcome to my beach getaway.
- It's beautiful.

11:19.504 --> 11:22.246
Ah, you know,
it's a perk of the job.

11:22.420 --> 11:24.161
It's been passed down
through the Roarke family

11:24.335 --> 11:27.687
for generations
like, you know, my hacienda.

11:29.558 --> 11:31.516
How have I never noticed
this place from the plane?

11:31.691 --> 11:34.432
It's Island Magic.

11:34.606 --> 11:35.651
You'll see it
now that you know it's here.

11:35.825 --> 11:37.653
- Mm.
- Mm-hmm.

11:41.439 --> 11:42.876
You know what?

11:43.050 --> 11:45.313
You are the first person
that I have ever brought here.

11:47.315 --> 11:48.882
- I'm honored.
- Mm.

11:49.056 --> 11:50.448
How many more secrets
do you have?

11:50.622 --> 11:52.102
Lots.

11:52.276 --> 11:54.235
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

11:54.409 --> 11:57.412
Well, I don't have any.
What you see is what you get.

11:57.586 --> 11:59.196
Well, it's a good thing
that I like what I see.

12:01.938 --> 12:04.593
Now, let's go over
that schedule.

12:04.767 --> 12:06.290
- Right now?
- Mm-hmm.

12:06.464 --> 12:08.336
Let's go.

12:10.120 --> 12:13.950
I am in the ocean.

12:14.124 --> 12:16.126
I'm not worried about
sharks or riptides.

12:16.300 --> 12:19.347
It's just water.

12:19.521 --> 12:21.175
This is amazing.

12:21.349 --> 12:22.959
Well, I mean,
I wouldn't say that you are

12:23.133 --> 12:27.485
technically in the ocean,
but yay.

12:27.659 --> 12:30.227
I wasted so much of
my life just thinking

12:30.401 --> 12:33.187
every little thing was the big,
bad monster under the bed.

12:33.361 --> 12:34.536
I only have two fears.

12:34.710 --> 12:36.799
Singing in public

12:36.973 --> 12:38.975
and being alone
for the rest of my life.

12:39.149 --> 12:40.977
One visceral,
one existential.

12:41.151 --> 12:43.545
Very respectable.

12:43.719 --> 12:44.851
Oh.

12:47.679 --> 12:50.073
It looks like Eli's having
the time of his life.

12:50.247 --> 12:51.727
Or he's trying to.

12:51.901 --> 12:54.121
See, the fantasies here

12:54.295 --> 12:56.079
can be a lot more layered
than they seem.

12:56.253 --> 12:59.082
But, have you decided on what
you're getting for your tattoo?

12:59.256 --> 13:00.910
No clue.

13:01.084 --> 13:03.043
How'd you decide on yours?

13:03.217 --> 13:05.393
Well, actually,
mine chose me.

13:05.567 --> 13:07.351
I got it at this little hut
that I'm taking you to.

13:07.525 --> 13:08.831
And had you
always wanted one?

13:09.005 --> 13:11.312
No. No, no, never.

13:11.486 --> 13:15.229
But there was this woman, Isla.
- Oh!

13:15.403 --> 13:18.232
And something called
Island Magic.

13:18.406 --> 13:21.322
And, well, the moment
was the moment.

13:21.496 --> 13:24.107
And this tattoo literally
became the dividing line

13:24.281 --> 13:28.372
between my old life
and my new one.

13:28.546 --> 13:30.897
I hope the same thing
is true for me.

13:31.071 --> 13:32.159
We're here.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.597
Okay.
- Yeah.

13:40.167 --> 13:42.517
Hey, there.
How can I help you?

13:42.691 --> 13:45.302
I want to get a tattoo.
A big one.

13:45.476 --> 13:48.915
Uh, you do realize
you can still feel pain, right?

13:49.089 --> 13:51.787
- Or, like, medium.
- Mm-hmm.

13:51.961 --> 13:53.441
Sure, man, I got you.

13:53.615 --> 13:55.660
Take a look.
See if something speaks to you.

13:55.835 --> 13:57.488
Okay.

13:57.662 --> 14:01.014
Um... I'm just wondering.
Is Isla working today?

14:01.188 --> 14:04.278
I don't know that name. Sorry.

14:04.452 --> 14:06.280
Isla.
She's got long, shiny hair.

14:06.454 --> 14:09.587
Brown eyes.
The sweet, soft, melodic voice.

14:09.761 --> 14:12.982
I've been here for years,
and there's no Isla.

14:13.156 --> 14:16.246
- Huh.
- How about this?

14:16.420 --> 14:18.858
Koi fish. Symbolizes courage.

14:19.032 --> 14:21.034
Perfect.
See? It chose you.

14:22.383 --> 14:25.603
Wise choice.
Take a seat, bro.

14:25.777 --> 14:28.041
Well, would you like me
to hold your hand through it?

14:28.215 --> 14:29.520
- I got this.
- Yeah?

14:29.694 --> 14:31.522
Yeah.
I'm fearless.

14:31.696 --> 14:32.872
Okay.

14:38.486 --> 14:40.096
That door
was supposed to be locked.

14:40.270 --> 14:41.619
We're closed for siesta.

14:41.793 --> 14:43.578
I've been on the road
for 39 hours.

14:43.752 --> 14:46.015
Take pity on me?
- Come back in an hour.

14:46.189 --> 14:48.539
Please,
just a bowl of paella?

14:48.713 --> 14:51.151
I happen to know that
you have a pot on the stove.

14:51.325 --> 14:53.109
Well, you're very
sure of yourself.

14:53.283 --> 14:56.069
I'm just really,
really hungry.

14:56.243 --> 14:58.549
Also...

14:58.723 --> 15:01.291
you might be the most beautiful
woman I've ever seen.

15:03.293 --> 15:05.513
And you're lucky
you have a nice smile.

15:08.298 --> 15:08.995
I'll get the paella.

15:21.311 --> 15:24.053
Hello, Helene.
Have a seat.

15:26.099 --> 15:28.884
Horchata.
Very popular here in Spain.

15:29.058 --> 15:30.320
She's not my mom.

15:30.494 --> 15:33.367
I know.
Her name is Camilla.

15:33.541 --> 15:36.239
She and Mateo spent a night
together in Barcelona in 2001.

15:38.589 --> 15:39.590
So that means
he's not my father.

15:39.764 --> 15:41.331
Oh, we don't know that
for sure.

15:41.505 --> 15:44.378
This is a snapshot.
It's not his whole life.

15:44.552 --> 15:46.162
What if my father
doesn't even remember my mom?

15:46.336 --> 15:47.772
Your mother doesn't sound

15:47.947 --> 15:50.253
like a woman
who'd be easily forgotten.

15:50.427 --> 15:51.776
And you know, people can make

15:51.951 --> 15:54.040
a big impact on us
in a very short time.

15:54.214 --> 15:56.216
Look at Mateo and Camilla.

15:56.390 --> 16:00.394
Their time together has
stayed with him all this time.

16:00.568 --> 16:02.439
I just hope
she meant something to him.

16:02.613 --> 16:04.964
My mom deserves that.

16:05.138 --> 16:07.836
You know,
I've never seen one guest

16:08.010 --> 16:10.621
follow another
into their fantasy.

16:10.795 --> 16:13.363
- Is it against the rules?
- There are no rules,

16:13.537 --> 16:17.759
